The United States has allocated over $134 million in assistance to support the Western Balkans' integration with the European Union and NATO. This assistance is aimed at accelerating rule of law and good governance reforms, professionalizing law enforcement, improving border security, supporting civil society and independent media, improving competitiveness of small and medium-sized enterprises, promoting conflict mitigation and reconciliation, integrating the region into Europe's energy networks, helping NATO aspirants fulfill requirements, strengthening vocational education, supporting the implementation of Kosovo-Serbia Dialogue agreements, and countering extremist messaging.